T1  - On the superneutrality of money in a stochastic dynamic macroeconomic model
AU  - Danthine, Jean-Pierre
AU  - Donaldson, John B.
AU  - Smith, Lance
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 20
IS  - 3
SP  - 475
EP  - 499
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/12/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(87)90038-9
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393287900389
AB  - This paper explores the robustness of the superneutrality of money result to the introduction of uncertainty. While, qualitatively, superneutrality fails to obtain in our model, quantitatively the observed Tobin effect is insignificant. The equilibrium time paths of real variables are nearly unaffected by changes in the money growth rule. We argue that our conclusions reinforce the theoretical case for superneutrality.
ER  - 
